# HSM collector conformance v1 — int bar aggregation contract.
# Format: case|action|arg1|arg2|...
# Bar actions:
# create_int_bar_sensor|path|bar_period_ms|post_period_ms   (post_period_ms=0 => inert periodic posting; BarTickPeriod is always inert)
# add_bar_int|bar_index|value
# add_bar_int_sequence|bar_index|count|start_value|step
# add_bar_int_parallel|bar_index|worker_count|values_per_worker|start_value   (worker w adds start + w*per_worker + i)
# add_int_bar_partial|bar_index|min|max|mean|first|last|count
# expect_bar_field|payload_index|field|expected   (payload_index=-1 => last; field: type|min|max|mean|first|last|count|status)
# expect_bar_open_close_aligned|payload_index|period_ms
# expect_bar_count_total|expected
# Contract notes:
# - The collector flushes a non-empty partial bar on Stop; empty bars never produce a payload.
# - Int bar mean is banker's rounding (round-half-to-even) of sum/count.
# - Bar values added before Start accumulate into the bar (unlike instant sensors, which drop).
# - Alignment asserts only use periods that divide the 0001->1970 epoch offset in ms.
# - Fixtures create only bar sensors, so bar_index matches dispose_sensor's global sensor index.

